The food here is not fresh . I ordered a talawa last night and IAM suffering from a bad stomach because of this stupid decision I made . Selling Stale food to cut losses is just unethical from the business point of view as well .

I ordered food from Hotel Alhamdulillah. Not only did they take a long time to prepare, but the food wasn't edible either. They didn't even add salt to it and the meat was undercooked. My friend vomited because of this.

I think that's the restaurant policy to sell anything..not taking care of customer health. The quality is so bad that, you will vomit by the smell of it.
Note- Zomato should take stern action on these partners who does not maintain the quality of food.

please don't get cheated by ordering from here. this is here only to ruin the Nampally Alhamdulillah's name. I ordered full talava ghost (Rs. 185) and it was not even half the quantity of the talava that you get from Nampally for Rs. 100.
